reviews.review_text:
a better version of a great show If you do nothing else check out the 3rd set but its all a tasty morsel of delicate flavors.

I love the Europe tour of 72' and this is one of its finest.

Bozos At The Tivoli A good, but not GREAT Europe '72 show. Even the merely "good" shows on that tour were exceptional though! Highlights are the China Cat>Rider, the first ever performance of He's Gone, a solid Truckin' and a blistering Big Railroad Blues. 
For those who haven't seen the video from this show, Big Railroad was played while the band wore Bozo masks for the TV cameras! During It Hurts Me Too the camera zooms in on Phil, head back eyes closed, playing bass with a joint in his mouth!
The third set Dark Star is more peaceful than most of the other Dark Stars of this tour, which makes it somewhat unique. Hardly the best from the tour, but still a nice listening experience.  
This is a good recording and the sound quality is excellent. If you get a chance to see the video you should check that out too .
doobie 5 stars for phil smokin the doob during it hurts me too
